# RealScout + IDX boundaries (Rhodes Ranch site)

## Do not confuse with IDX

- **`components/idx/**`** — MLS/IDX compliance. **Do not edit** unless the user explicitly requests it.
- **`components/realscout/**`** — RealScout web components and lead strips. This is the correct place for office listing widgets.

## Script: load once (client loader)

- Load RealScout UMD **once** via **`lib/realscout-load.ts`** (`ensureRealScoutReady()`), called from **`RealScoutOfficeListings`**. Do **not** add a second script in **`app/layout.tsx`** or pages.
- **Never** use `type="module"` on the UMD file — it is not an ES module; module mode breaks the widget.

## Widget markup: per route by default

- **`RealScoutOfficeListings`** mounts `<realscout-office-listings>` with **`createElement` + `setAttribute`** after `ensureRealScoutReady()` (see component).
- **Do not** mount the full MLS lead strip in **root `layout.tsx`** unless the user explicitly asks for a site-wide block. Prefer importing **`RealScoutLeadSection`** (or the listings component) on **`app/**/page.tsx`** where each route needs it—usually **below the page hero**—to control weight, SEO, and layout.
- Avoid duplicating the **same** strip twice on one URL (layout + page).

## CSP

- When changing RealScout or embeds, keep **`next.config.ts`** CSP in sync: `script-src` / `connect-src` for `em.realscout.com` and `www.realscout.com`, and any `frame-src` / `wss:` hosts the widget needs.
